metadata.name: Towers of Power #32
metadata.description:
In this generative art illustration, I wanted to represent the power of the upper class against as tall towers against and covering a starred sky. 
I sketched the towers with vertical and horizontal lines, circles, and ellipses to represent the power and control that they have. 
A light, transparent and, yet big, sun is sketched in the background to represent the hope that the poor and minorities have for justice and a better world.

This illustration is created within my research effort to recreate in the digital medium my style of physical acrylic painting that uses paint drips on technical drawings and textured background.

Three modes: dark, light and gold.
Many form factors.

Hit 's' to save a svg
Hit 'p' to save a png

metadata.name: Tumble Down Light Factory #4
metadata.description:
Tumble Down Light Factory is an interpretation of light installations & murals.

It attempts to trigger the feeling of coming up on a new block in a new city to discover an unexpected piece of art that is stories tall or entering a new room, knowing there will be a projection dominating the space with its light and color.

This is an abstract distillation of those things and those feelings.

Each composition is initially drawn to a hidden “template” canvas which is sampled and then rendered on the main canvas in various ways after applying some transforms to give it some depth (and so you can actually see it.)

Viewing in full-screen is nice. You should try it.

T : Save hidden ‘template’ image
S : Save current resolution
1 -> 5 : Save low -> high resolution

metadata.name: Nounfall #377
metadata.description:
Nounfall is drawn exclusively from the 234 heads and 21 glasses that are used to build the current Nouns collection. The background colors are all pulled from the blessed Noun palette.

This is ok because Nouns are CC0, which basically means public domain. Check out nouns.wtf for more info.

They make for fun social media banners when cropped, if you wanna show off you fandom of Nouns.

C : Clear screen and start animation over
S : Save current image
1 -> 6 : Set pixel density to the respective number

So, if you want a high resolution file, tap `6` for it to redraw, and then `S` to save. You can also save while it's animating if you like, which is fun too.

metadata.name: cliques #50
metadata.description:
clique is defined as:

- /klēk,klik/ (n.) a small group of people, with shared interests or other features in common, who spend time together and do not readily allow others to join them.

cliques can offer safety. (something about numbers.)

cliques can offer a place to be. (for better or worse.)

sometimes cliques have sub-cliques. (the intersections can get a bit complicated.)

sometimes a member of a clique may still feel outside of it. (power dynamics can ruin things.)

occasionally clique dynamics are balanced and the connections between the members pull towards the center. (we can consider that non-toxic.)

often, though, the connections are pulled in various directions and the connection between two members are swayed (or pulled towards) other members. (we can consider that toxic.)

[4 color palettes: monochrome, neon, vibrant rebellion, glacier]

[tap “s” to save image]
[tip: zoom out to 25% first to save a higher res image]

[cc0] [p5js] [xoxo] [twitter: @heyjeres]

metadata.name: Hayata! #51
metadata.description:
Hayata! emerged from my brief research on one-dimensional cellular automata (CA) and developed into a full project, since the resulting patterns were much more interesting than I had expected, especially when you mix the rules together.
Since the rules of this CA are so simple, they have something ancient, original and mysterious about them, like the I-Ching or other oracle methods. So I tried to give the CA a worthy frame by making the texture look aged and handmade.
I hope that your oracle only predicts good things for you :)
------
F.D. Berlin, October '22

Size: Between 1600px and 3200px both height and width.
Libraries used: chroma.js

metadata.name: TENDER Pass #439
metadata.description:
Tender is a curatorial platform and community that helps bring incredible works of generative art to discerning collectors.

Holding a TENDER Pass enables enriched benefits and experiences within the Tender ecosystem. Passholders expand their access to unique collaborations with extraordinary artists, indispensable collector tools, curatorial experiences, artwork insights, fine art prints, a thriving community, and more.

Tender is committed to stewarding the growth of generative art and amplifying the voices of artists and collectors across the entire lifecycle: from creation to collection to curation, and back again. Every Pass minted and resold directly enables Tender to continue creating the platform and experiences that serve this mission.

——

TENDER Pass features unique artwork by punevyr. While all Passes are special, a small number of randomly generated, rarified tokens will come with boosted benefits. If you have a piece with a dark background of any kind, you likely possess one of the following:

Bonus Pass
TENDER Passes with the special Bonus trait get 1 guaranteed reserve spot on all TENDER x Collab projects

Grail Pass
TENDER Passes with the special Grail trait get 2 free mints on all TENDER x Collab projects


New Passholders may access our Discord server that’s linked from our website.
For TENDER Pass benefits and up-to-date details, please visit tender.art/pass


Artwork created with p5.js

---

TENDER x punevyr
July 2022

metadata.name: VOODOOZ #253
metadata.description:
Need some luck, happiness, and lucky charm? Alexis Bacci’s VOODOOZ are here for you! Will you dare to mint and to collect?

VOODOOZ is a collection of 512 magical dolls of 3 types: basic, collector and boss - with or without accessories; a tribute to Voodoo culture entirely hand drawn by the comics author Alexis Bacci.

Each VOODOOZ doll has specific and unique magical powers, bringing luck and happiness, a lucky charm in your journey in the NFTs world!

Voodooz come with optional accessories: the SNAKE, the POTION and the RING.

• The SNAKE can complete the inner circle of life and vital energy
• The POTION will help the doll to spell, protect and increase its skills
• The RING gives more power and can be used as a talisman
• The HOLY TRINITY gathers the 3 accessories above

Tip: try to grab a SNAKE + a POTION + a RING and a special VOODOOZ NFT will be airdropped to your wallet for free.

Alexis Bacci is a comics book author who has been working in the cartoon and movie industry for two decades. In 2021 he minted his 1st NFTs on ETH, the Tengu Diaries, and his Girlz series on Tezos.

VOODOOZ are Alexis’ genesis series on fx(hash), pay attention!

metadata.name: Computational Decay #2
metadata.description:
The internet, seems to have been a sensation of the past civilization, nobody knows what the old folks were thinking when they were building it all. Sounds like a candyland for sure with free games, pirated movies just for the price of your attention. Maybe that was a better model than the one we have now. It's 2074 or the 25th year after the collapse of the world wide web. There are still many old people who remember instances from those days, the ones who lived through the collapse to tell the tale. But the fact is nobody knows what exactly triggered it. Imagine a civilization reliant on their networks suddenly loosing the power to access it and boom....there was chaos everywhere. 

Now things have settled but the web doesn't exist anymore. But we do have decentralized hubs running their own shit like marketplaces, services, custom softwares and what not with the flavours transforming with every city or town that you might visit. And sometimes the occasional fun stuff from the great beyond. And yeah, apparently the rich pay good money to us, the scavengers of the older network. Its a scary place and so very easy to lose yourself in it without the proper skills. I heard earlier people would just gaze at their screens to lose themselves in it... Now all we need to do is log in to the cyber deck, dive into our cryostation and make the jump! 

- - - - - - - - - - 

Press 'S' to take a screenshot
Press 'D' to toggle resolution | Default 4096x2160 | Alternatively 8192x4320 | use with caution its heavy
Press 'A' to animate

- - - - - - - - - -  

All holders of 'Chaos' have a reserve, which will be released a few days after minting opens. 
Happy Minting! 

Made with Cables.gl 
Jaalibandar '23

metadata.name: Minimal Monoliths #68
metadata.description:
Minimal Monoliths is a work mainly inspired by the use of AI as a creative tool.  I have a new fixation with monoliths as simple minimal structures just placed on random surfaces, so I iterated quite a few illustrations to sense the variations of shapes. 

Once I had an idea of what I wanted, I translated it into code creating something minimal with very fine lines that flow and then at some random point are disrupted by an emerging element.

Then in order to add volume and create a sense of depth, I increased the number of lines per iteration.

As Monoliths are considered elements deeply connected with nature I wanted to keep the lines and backgrounds within the spectrum of the earth's colors.

9 Color Palettes 
4 Backgrounds
Lines count [23,31,41,59,67,79,89,97,109] 

Made with ❤️ & pj5s

By CodeNFT (Clementine Novak)
October 2022
